{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "The main contributions and the differences are as follows.",
    "(1) A quantum-like sentence tensor representation for the text, which incorporates both semantic and syntactic information of adjacent words, is proposed to accentuate the local semantic contribution of adjacent word pairs.",
    "(2) The distinct weights for the different PoS combinations of adjacent words and semantic similarity are defined as the semantic influence factors to emphasize the semantic contribution of shared modifications and common phrases in the text.",
    "(3) We reduce the redundant information brought by tensor expansion via the optimization constraints to optimize the sentence representation.",
    "(4) We discuss the impact of the provided model on semantic similarity calculation at two different levels of granularity: the corpus level and the sentence level."
  ],
